    public interface Printable
    Any class implementing this interface can print its data. Every class provides a default way of printing itself as source code. The class may also support overriding the default behavior at the class level. For example, the pass writer may wish all ForStatements to be printed in a certain way. It may also support overriding the behavior for a particular object. For example, once a pass determines that a loop is parallel, it may need to modify the print behavior for that loop only. For consistency, changing the print method of a class or object will also affect the behavior of toString for that class or object.

    • Method Detail

      • print

        void print​(java.io.PrintWriter o)
        Print the code for the IR represented by the object. Always calls object_print_method(this, o). If the object's print method is null, nothing is printed; this provides an easy mechanism to temporarily hide something.
        Parameters:
        o - The writer on which to print the data.
